oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Log home
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Mr. & Mrs. W.H. Morris in front of their log home, proudly exhibiting their home food supply records for R.T. Nichols, Farm Security Supervisor for Davidson and Williamson Counties. A swing is in front of the house.
The Home Food Supply Program was a war-relief program instituted by the administration of Gov. Prentice Cooper. The Morrises rented a 72-acre farm.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Tennessee Department of Conservation Photograph Collection, 1937-1976
